        "title": "feat(i18n): add native app locale inventory",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe Control UI has a translation pipeline, but native Android and Apple surfaces are not yet visible to the same i18n checks. That makes it easy to add Russian or Hindi support while silently leaving app UI strings outside the translation process.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd a deterministic native-app string inventory covering Android Compose and SwiftUI/UIKit-facing Apple sources. The inventory is generated from source, checked in CI, and gives the follow-up platform PRs a stable input surface for the existing provider, glossary, cache, and locale-refresh process.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo runtime strings change in this PR. CI now detects native-app i18n inventory drift when Android or Apple app code changes.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm test:serial test/scripts/native-app-i18n.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check scripts/native-app-i18n.ts test/scripts/native-app-i18n.test.ts package.json scripts/test-projects.test-support.mjs .github/workflows/ci.yml`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nAI-assisted implementation; the generated inventory is deterministic and reviewable.\n",
